<H1 align=center>Bibliography of<BR>
CSS <I>Virginia</I> (Merrimack)<BR>
vs USS <I>Monitor</I></H1>
		<P>See the numerous historical documents listing at</P>
		<ul>
					<li><A HREF="../../vacsn4/original/index.htm">Original references</A>
		</ul>
		<p>See also our bibliographies for</p>
		<ul>
					<li><A HREF="biblio-other.htm#civil war">American Civil War</A>
					<li><A HREF="biblio-other.htm#CaRJ">Catesby ap Roger Jones</A>
					<li><A HREF="biblio-other.htm#TaCJ">Thomas ap Catesby Jones</A>
					<li><A HREF="biblio-other.htm#navy">19th Century Navy</A>
		</ul>
		<P>Other relevant bibliographies available on the Internet:</P>
		<ul>
					<li><a href="http://www.monitorcenter.org/resources/bibliographies/scopearrange/" target="x">A Monitor Bibliography</a> at the Mariners' Museum (excellent!)
					<li><A TARGET=x HREF="http://www.history.navy.mil/biblio/biblio1/biblio1k.htm">Civil War bibliography</A> at the Naval Historical Center

					<li><A TARGET=x HREF="http://ahecwebdds.carlisle.army.mil/awapps/main.jsp?flag=browse&smd=2&awdid=6">Hampton Roads bibliography</A> at the US Army Military History Institute
					<ul>
						<li><A TARGET=x HREF="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/academic/history/marshall/military/mil_hist_inst/c/cw7a.asc">Textual version</A> at the MIL-HIST site (older version)
					</ul>
		</ul>
		<p>Other bibliographies:</p>
		<ul>
					<li><A HREF="#SmithDR68">Hampton Roads battle bibliography</A> by David Smith
					<li><A HREF="#WattsGP79">USS <I>Monitor</I> bibliography </A>by Gordon Watts
					<li><A HREF="#HarbeckCT06">US Navy bibliography</A> by Charles Harbeck.
		</ul>
		<p>When possible, I'm including a hyperlink to some library listing the book. For some books, I will list the libraries where I've seen it in their catalogues. See the <A HREF="#abbr">bottom</A> of the page for abbreviations. (I don't necessarily mark all books below in all the libraries below.)</p>
		<p><img src="../../myicons/eye.gif" alt="eye" width="19" height="11" border="0" align="left">Indicates a link to the Historical Documents (eyewitnesses) pages.</p>
